{"name": "pmr2-wfctrl", "metadata": {"name": "pmr2.wfctrl", "version": "0.7.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "http://github.com/PMR/pmr2.wfctrl", "license": "gpl", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["setuptools"], "summary": "Workflow controller", "upload_time": 1722576575}, "documentation": ["# Introduction\n\nA basic and light-weight workspace manager for PMR. While this package\nwill ultimately be usable as a general purpose library, for now features\nare targeted for integration by the MAP client.\n\n```{image} https://github.com/PMR2/pmr2.wfctrl/actions/workflows/build.yml/badge.svg?branch=0.7.0\n:target: https://github.com/PMR2/pmr2.wfctrl/actions/workflows/build.yml?query=branch:0.7.0\n```\n\n```{image} https://coveralls.io/repos/PMR2/pmr2.wfctrl/badge.svg?branch=0.7.0\n:target: https://coveralls.io/r/PMR2/pmr2.wfctrl?branch=0.7.0\n```\n\n# Changelog\n\n## 0.7.0 - 2024-08-02\n\n- Provide subclasses of existing commmands that allow credentials be\n  provided for accessing private workspaces.\n\n## 0.6.0 - 2023-10-17\n\n- Ensure that Dulwich methods return values match closer with the\n  cli command class counterpart.\n- Cleaned up support code in testing to ensure the defaults are not\n  interfered with.\n\n## 0.5.0 - 2023-10-06\n\n- Dulwich is now registered first.\n- Have the registration by name show all available implementations.\n\n## 0.4.0 - 2023-06-16\n\n- Updated Dulwich support to use official release.\n- Ensure that the workspace workflows will return the error code for the\n  external tools and not just assume stderr output are errors.\n\n## 0.3 - 2016-09-08\n\n- Support the use of a custom fork of Dulwich for Git access.\n\n## 0.2 - 2014-07-14\n\n- Renaming to the standard top-level namespace for this group of\n  packages.\n\n## 0.1 - 2013-12-18\n\n- Initial release.\n- Core support for basic incremental workflow management using both git\n  and mercurial.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.utils.set_url_cred", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "username", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "password", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "_protocols", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.testing", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pmr2.wfctrl", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.Requirement", "xref": {"fqname": "pkg_resources.Requirement", "project": "setuptools"}}, {"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.working_set", "xref": {"fqname": "pkg_resources.working_set", "project": "setuptools"}}]}, {"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.testing.base", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.testing.base.handle_access_error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exc_info", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Error handler for `shutil.rmtree`.\n\nIf the error is due to an access error (read only file)\nit attempts to add write permission and then retries.\n\nIf the error is for another reason it re-raises the error.\n\nUsage : `shutil.rmtree(path, onerror=onerror)`\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.testing.base.CoreTestCase", "bases": ["TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.testing.base.CoreTestCase.setUp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pmr2.wfctrl.testing.base.CoreTestCase.tearDown", "asynchronous": false, "para